{MBPS Modification ‒ Note to Chapter 1:  Local jurisdictions are responsible for the implementation
and enforcement of the Maryland Building Performance Standards.  Refer to each local jurisdiction for
local amendments to Chapter 1 of the IBC.  Each local jurisdiction having authority shall establish ...
implementation and enforcement procedures that include: (a) review and acceptance of appropriate plans;
(b) issuance of   building permits; (c) inspection of the work authorized by the building permits; and
(d) issuance of use and occupancy certificates.}

